



Dear Sir,
Fred[ericksbur]g 6th Apl 1774



Your favour of 28th March relating to the Land adjoining Mr Hunters I should have acknowledgd last Week; but had hopes of seeing you here at the Race1The Terms of Two Thousand Pounds will suit me at five annual paymentsI expect to discharge the Debt sooner, but as you are willing to let the money remain in my hands on Interestwill accept of that IndulgenceBe so good to inform me when I may be put in possession or when it will suit you to make the Conveyance. I am very respectfully Dr Sir Your most obedt St

Hugh Mercer

